YzUQbT5V224PHQEEwBuMsUXsJPd3qEAKns47TBoplKzu9Uik50l5mikomukzW9k0J2sXSFP-gPW=
qacFw" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">Two Centuries =
of Innovation and Stock Market Bubbles</a>, </em>shows a strong relationshi=
p between bubbles and innovation. The paper covers inventions from the stea=
m engine train (1825) to the smartphone (2000). Here&#8217;s how it works:&=
nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3=
=2E75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bulle=
t;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">New technologies comes to market=
,&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-for=
mat: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0;">People get over-excited and pour money into the companies th=
at commercialized them,</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px;=
 mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">The influx of cash accelerates the speed of =
development and adoption of new technologies,</p></li><li style=3D"margin: =
3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1=
a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Even when the bubble e=
nds, the companies that commercialized innovation outperform the market.</p=
></li></ul><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Demand for shares of companies taking risks on new tech=
nologies is reflexive: more money creates better technology which creates m=
ore demand for the stock, and so on. Believing in the product and wanting i=
t to exist actually helps bring it into existence.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Additi=
onally, big, splashy liquidity events and soaring prices pull the next gene=
ration of innovation forward, indirectly and directly.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D=
"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><s=
trong>Indirectly</strong>, they inspire the next generation of entrepreneur=
s to take their shot. So many multi-billion dollar companies have been foun=
ded within the past decade that creating the next one seems feasible.&nbsp;=
</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 1em 0;"><strong>Directly</strong>, they&#8217;ve created thousands of =
tech millionaires who want to invest in the next generation of unicorns. Th=
ey&#8217;ve seen that it&#8217;s possible and that the outcomes can be huge=
=2E If their idiot bosses could do it, s=
ome young, hungry genius can <em>defi=
nitely</em> do it. As one small proof point: in the past few weeks, a wave =
of people from recently-public tech companies have joined the <a href=3D"ht=
